# Graphite
A notepad-style software that can be used inside your terminal! Supports Mac, Windows, and Linux. <br>
<br>

# Install
Make sure to download `latest.js` in the program folder, get Node.js (if you haven't already), and run these commands: (make sure to replace "(type-in-your-folder-path)" with your folder path!)
```bash
cd (type-in-your-folder-path)
node Graphite.js
```

# Formatting
Quick note: the tags can be used in combination but the <reset> tag is required at the end of each format you would like to finish.
Tags that cannot be used in the Mac terminal correctly will be labeled with ❌🍏. <br>
Since some tags use unsupported ANSI codes, some are unusable for certain platforms and will be labeled accordingly. <br>
<br>
Use these tags for colored text:
```python
<green> # Makes text green.
<blue> # Makes text blue.
<red> # Makes text red.
<cyan> # Makes text cyan.
<magenta> # Makes text magenta.
<yellow> # Makes text yellow.
<white> # Makes text white.
<black> # Makes text black.
```
There is also a collection of other tags for lighter colors:
```python
<lgreen> # Makes text light-green.
<lblue> # Makes text light-blue.
<lred> # Makes text light-red.
<lcyan> # Makes text light-cyan.
<lmagenta> # Makes text light-magenta.
<lyellow> # Makes text light-yellow.
<lwhite> # Makes text light-white.
<lblack> # Makes text light-black.
```
There are also tags that can be used to change the background color of certain text:
```python
<hgreen> # Makes the background of text green.
<hblue> # Makes the background of text blue.
<hred> # Makes the background of text red.
<hcyan> # Makes the background of text cyan.
<hmagenta> # Makes the background of text magenta.
<hyellow> # Makes the background of text yellow.
<hwhite> # Makes the background of text white.
<hblack> # Makes the background of text black.
```
There are also tags that can be used to change the background color of certain text:
```python
<hlgreen> # Makes the background of text light-green.
<hlblue> # Makes the background of text light-blue.
<hlred> # Makes the background of text light-red.
<hlcyan> # Makes the background of text light-cyan.
<hlmagenta> # Makes the background of text light-magenta.
<hlyellow> # Makes the background of text light-yellow.
<hlwhite> # Makes the background of text light-white.
<hlblack> # Makes the background of text light-black.
```
There are also tags for formatting text and not changing the color:
```python
<italic> # Makes text italic. (❌🍏)
<dim> # Dims text.
<underline> # Underlines text.
<bold> # Makes text bold.
<strikethrough> # Makes text have a strikethrough. (❌🍏)
```
There are also help tags which can help you in certain ways:
```python
<help> # Shows useful help information.
```

More tags will be released in version 1.1 JS, so stay tuned!<br>
Happy notetaking!

